  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --sbindir=/sbin \
            --sysconfdir=/etc \
            --disable-static \
            --enable-split-usr \
            --enable-libkmod \
            --enable-rule-generator \
            --with-rootlibdir=/lib \
            --with-rootprefix= \
            --with-firmware-path=/lib/firmware &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install &amp;&amp;
ln -svf /sbin/udevd /lib/udev</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Create some directories that eudev cannot handle due to them being
      required very early in the boot process, or by eudev itself:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>install -dv /lib/{firmware,udev/devices/pts}</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install LFS-specific file used to configure eudev:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>cat > /etc/udev/rules.d/55-lfs.rules &lt;&lt; EOF
<literal># /etc/udev/rules.d/55-lfs.rules: Rule definitions for LFS.

# Core kernel devices

# This causes the system clock to be set as soon as /dev/rtc becomes available.
SUBSYSTEM=="rtc", ACTION=="add", MODE="0644", RUN+="/etc/rc.d/init.d/setclock start"
KERNEL=="rtc", ACTION=="add", MODE="0644", RUN+="/etc/rc.d/init.d/setclock start"

# Comms devices

KERNEL=="ippp[0-9]*",       GROUP="dialout"
KERNEL=="isdn[0-9]*",       GROUP="dialout"
KERNEL=="isdnctrl[0-9]*",   GROUP="dialout"
KERNEL=="dcbri[0-9]*",      GROUP="dialout"</literal>
EOF</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--enable-rule_generator</parameter>: This switch allows
        persistent rules to be generated for network and optical media devices.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--disable-gudev</option>: Use this switch if you want to disable
        Gobject libudev support.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--disable-keymap</option>: Use this switch if you want to
        disable keymap fixup support.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Configuration</title>

    <sect3 id="eudev-init">
      <title>Boot Script</title>

      <para>
        If you want to replace BusyBox mdev applet with eudev, install the eudev
        init scripts included in the <xref linkend="bootscripts"/> package and
        reboot the system.
      </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install-eudev</userinput></screen>

      <para>
        To revert back to mdev, uninstall the eudev init scripts and reboot the
        system.
      </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make uninstall-eudev</userinput></screen>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

